    <p>Hi <br> How are you?</p>

    <!-- Styled Paragraph -->
    <p class="styled-text">This is a colored and styled paragraph.</p>

    <!-- Title Attribute Example -->
    <p title="language">This is a title for the paragraph.</p>
    <p title='title is "RITHU" for this paragraph'>This paragraph has a title attribute.</p>
    <h2 title='John "ShotGun" Nelson'>Heading with Title</h2>

    <hr>

    <!-- Heading Tags -->
    <h1>Halleyx</h1>
    <h2>Halleyx</h2>
    <h3>Halleyx</h3>
    <h4>Halleyx</h4>
    <h5>Halleyx</h5>
    <h6>Halleyx</h6>

    <!-- Inline Styling Example -->
    <h1 style="font-family: 'Franklin Gothic Medium', 'Arial Narrow', Arial, sans-serif; font-size: large;">Hi</h1>

    <hr>

    <!-- Paragraph with Line Break -->
    <p>
        This website is only for reference to what I have learned today. It's not any official website. <br>
        That's all about the paragraph tag in HTML.
    </p>

    <!-- HR Example -->
    <p>This website is only for reference to what I have learned today. It's not any official.</p>
    <hr>
    <p>That's all about paragraph tags in HTML.</p>

    <!-- Line Breaks -->
    <p>Hi <br> How are you? <br> Nice to meet you.</p>

    <!-- Poem Example -->
    <pre>
I think I will miss you forever, like
a star misses the sun in the morning sky.
Later is better than never,
even if you're gone, I'm gonna drive alone.
    </pre>

    <hr>

